data.enText: the distance of a place north or south of the equator (= the line around the world dividing north and south) , measured in degrees
a region of the world that is a particular distance from the equator

data.chText: 选择（做什么事或做事方式）的自由
data.enText: freedom to choose what you do or the way that you do it

simple_means.memory_skill: lat 宽 + itude 状态 → 纬度之间距离很宽 → 纬度

means: 选择(做什么事或做事方式)的自由

tr: scope for freedom of e.g. action or thought
the angular distance between an imaginary line around a heavenly body parallel to its equator and the equator itself
an imaginary line around the Earth parallel to the equator
freedom from normal restraints in conduct
example: the new freedom in movies and novels
allowed his children considerable latitude in how they spent their money

value.def: The latitude of a place is its distance from the equator.

example.ex: In the middle to high latitudes rainfall has risen steadily over the last 20-30 years.
example.tran: 在过去二三十年里，中高纬度地区的降雨量持续增加。

example.ex: The army must cease military operations above 36 degrees latitude north.
example.tran: 在北纬36度以北地区，军队必须停止军事行动。

value.def: Latitude is freedom to choose the way in which you do something.

example.ex: He would be given every latitude in forming a new government...
example.tran: 他将可以不受任何限制地组建新政府。

example.ex: His status at the studio afforded him all the artistic latitude he could ask for.
example.tran: 他在创作室的地位让他可以在艺术上自由探索。
